  "text": "The inter-broker replication protocol in apache/kafka spans Java and Scala files. Key Java source files:\n\n**ReplicaFetcherThread**: The main ReplicaFetcherThread class is in Scala (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaFetcherThread.scala), but the Java companion `TierStateMachine.java` handles tiered-storage state transitions during fetching, and `ReplicaManagerBuilder.java` builds the ReplicaManager that orchestrates fetcher threads.\n\n**LeaderEpochFileCache**: Implemented in `LeaderEpochFileCache.java` with supporting `EpochEntry.java` (epoch/offset pairs) and `LeaderEpochCheckpointFile.java` (persistence to disk).\n\n**LogStartOffset tracking**: `UnifiedLog.java` is the main log abstraction that tracks and increments logStartOffset. `LogStartOffsetIncrementReason.java` enumerates reasons for advancement. `LocalLog.java` manages the underlying segment-level log. `LogLoader.java` recovers logStartOffset on startup. `LogOffsetSnapshot.java` captures the offset state (including logStartOffset) for fetch responses. `ProducerStateManager.java` truncates producer state based on logStartOffset. `RemoteLogManager.java` handles logStartOffset for tiered storage.\n\n**ISR shrink/expand**: The controller-side ISR management is in `ReplicationControlManager.java` (processes AlterPartition requests for ISR changes) and `PartitionChangeBuilder.java` (builds ISR change records). `LeaderAndIsr.java` and `PartitionRegistration.java` hold ISR state. The broker-side ISR logic (maybeShrinkIsr/maybeExpandIsr) lives in Scala files Partition.scala and ReplicaManager.scala. `LogReadResult.java`, `Replica.java`, and `FetchPartitionData.java` carry fetch/replica state used in ISR evaluation.",
